    <h2>Riddells Creek Chimney and Flue Cleaning</h2>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>Riddells Creek is a small township in the Macedon Ranges, sitting in the Riddells Creek valley between Gisborne and Romsey — proper Macedon Ranges country with cold winters, regular frosts and a genuine country town character. The Bendigo train line runs through, making it part of Melbourne's outer commuter belt, but the feel remains distinctly rural. Properties range from older township homes on the main streets to rural residential estates that developed through the 1990s and 2000s, and most rely on wood heating through a winter that runs longer and colder than in Melbourne's metro suburbs. Cold air drains off the surrounding ranges overnight, pushing temperatures well below the Melbourne average from May to August. We cover Riddells Creek on our regular Gisborne and Macedon Ranges run.</p>
